{"name": "test-results-parser", "metadata": {"name": "test-results-parser", "version": "0.5.1", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: PyPy", "Programming Language :: Rust"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1728416264}, "documentation": ["This project requires `maturin`, it can be installed using pip:\n```pip install maturin```\n\nFor development, to rebuild the rust portion of the library and install the library in your local venv (I believe this _requires_ a venv in order to work), run:\n```maturin develop```\n\nTo use the library just import it after installing:\n```import testing_result_parsers```\n\nThere's an example of this in the tests directory.\n\nThe CI uses the maturin-action to build wheels and an sdist\n\nThe version of the wheels built are determined by the value of the version in the cargo.toml\n\nThere are 2 parsing function currently implemented:\n\n- `parse_junit_xml`: this parses `junit.xml` files\n- `parse_pytest_reportlog`: this parses files produced by the `pytest-reportlog` extension\n\nBoth these functions take the path to the file to parse as an arg and return a list of `Testrun` objects.\n\nThe `Testrun` objects look like this:\n```\nOutcome:\n    Pass,\n    Failure,\n    Error,\n    Skip\n\nTestrun:\n    name: str\n    outcome: Outcome\n    duration: float\n    testsuite: str\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "tests.test_failure_message", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "tests.test_failure_message.test_shorten_file_paths", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.test_shorten_file_paths_short_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.test_shorten_file_paths_long_path", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.test_shorten_file_paths_long_path_leading_slash", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.test_build_message_no_failures", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.test_build_message", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tests.test_failure_message.TestRunsPayload", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "tests.test_failure_message.TestRunsPayload.failed", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.TestRunsPayload.passed", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.TestRunsPayload.skipped", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.TestRunsPayload.failures", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.Run", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "tests.test_failure_message.Run.name", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.Run.testsuite", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.Run.failure_message", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "tests.test_failure_message.Run.duration", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "tests.test_junit", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "tests.test_junit.TestParsers", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "tests.test_junit.TestParsers.test_junit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "expected", "type": null, "defa